## Architecture

This project uses **Nuxt 4** with auto-imports and file-based conventions:

- **app/** — All application code (Vue components, pages, layouts)
- **app/pages/** — File-based routing (each `.vue` file is a route)
- **server/** — Nitro server engine (API routes, server middleware)
- **server/api/** — Auto-registered API endpoints
- **stores/** — Pinia state management (auto-imported)
- **app/composables/** — Auto-imported Vue composables
- **app/components/** — Auto-imported Vue components

Key conventions:

- `app/pages/` drives routing — create a file, get a route
- API routes in `server/api/` return JSON automatically
- Pinia stores go in `stores/` and are auto-imported by name
- Composables in `app/composables/` are auto-imported
- `app/app.vue` is the root component (use `<NuxtLayout>` and `<NuxtPage>`)
- Layouts in `app/layouts/` wrap pages (use `<NuxtLayout>` in app.vue)
